In the higher and more central parts, the second great division of the race, that of the Hermiones, was spread, the tribes of which spoke Upper or Hiyh-Geman dialects. Begin- ing in the West with the country of the Sigambri on the Rhino, and from that of the Cherusci and Angrivarii near the Weser and the Har-tz, this division comprehended, besides those tribes, the Chatti, the Langobardi, the Hermunduri, the Marcomanni and Quadi, the Lugii, and beyond the Vistula the Bastarnae, in the neighborhood of the Carpathian 111118.
